    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Recently, neovim adds more third-party dependencies. You can find them [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/third-party/CMakeLists.txt#L73-L83). All of them are from neovim forked dependencies. Therefore, I have following questions:\n- Is it necessary to have neovim forking these repo as it will add workload to sync them with upstream changes?\n- The deps' urls are not versionized. So any changes in that branch will break the checksum, hence break the building.\n\n/cc @tarruda  \n",
