            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I'm not sure how the mirroring is set up, but it's feasible that we only need to update when we trip across a bug for now and when a real release is available that works we can drop our mirror.\n\nI mirrored manually using git-bzr.\n\nBut the main reason I forked libtickit/libtermkey was to avoid spending bandwidth on @leonerd's server, and the only [github mirrors](https://github.com/o11c/libtickit) I found are very outdated.\n\nUnibilium was mirrored because of yesterday fixes, but it seems the developer has already pushed a tag with it so the mirror is no longer necessary.\n",
